; Import definitions for the AviSynth+ C-API functions the plugin calls. A MinGW
; cross-build uses this with dlltool to generate an import library, so the .dll
; links without needing the (MSVC-built) AviSynth.dll or its .lib at build time.
; The LIBRARY name is what the plugin's import table references; at load time the
; host AviSynth resolves it. Only AVSC_API entries need importing - the AVSC_INLINE
; value helpers (avs_defined, avs_as_string, avs_array_elt, avs_new_value_error, ...)
; are header-only. Keep in sync with the avs_* calls in avisynth_plugin.c.
LIBRARY AviSynth.dll
EXPORTS
avs_add_function
avs_new_c_filter
avs_set_to_clip
avs_release_clip
avs_new_video_frame_a
avs_get_pitch_p
avs_get_write_ptr_p
avs_save_string
avs_release_video_frame
